this is probably a cliche question but how do i lose weight on my hips the bad news is that if you want to lose weight on your hips you have to lose it everywhere else too the good news is that hourglass figures are hot anyway you lose weight on your hips by losing weight all over the simplest way to do that is to eat less and exercise more be sure to include cardio and strength training muscle ups your metabolism makes you stronger and takes up less space than fat try yoga or pilates to work on strengthening your core bear in mind that you probably inherited your shape and won't be able to spot reduce without surgery of some kind while you're waiting around for the diet exercise to start showing its effectiveness focus on wearing flattering clothing that makes you feel sexy Weight training Bodybuilding Exercise Dieting Corset Urinary incontinence Prostate cancer Osteoarthritis Equine conformation Obesity Tightlacing Tocopherol Pilates Non-Hodgkin's lymphoma Ayurveda Swimming Insulin Weight loss Diabetes mellitus Hormone replacement therapy (trans) Fecal incontinence Anorexia nervosa The Ashlee Simpson Show Gangsta rap Jennifer Lopez Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Aerobic exercise Osteoporosis Low-carbohydrate diet Sexual attraction Brassiere Hip dysplasia Iliotibial band syndrome Social rule Replacement joint Massage Binge eating disorder Growth hormone Meditation Body type (exercise) Mattress Rhythm and blues Myopia Glossary of partner dance terms Game show Paget's disease of bone Thermoregulation Domestic rabbit Nuclear weapon design Hip hop culture Climbing equipment Carpal tunnel syndrome Les Mills Atherosclerosis Brain Protein Japanese tea ceremony Welding Hypoglycemia Judo Puberty Aikido Physical attractiveness Weight Watchers Breastfeeding The Amazing Race Hypertension Hourglass corset Muay Thai Coronary heart disease Repetitive strain injury Eye Undergarment Strap-on dildo Yoga Folic acid Chocolate Creatine Wonder Woman (television series) Stomach cancer Androgen